This paper deals with the problem of machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of machine learning techniques and morphological features also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML). The focus on ranking and validation of results indicates the use of information retrieval (IR) techniques. The use of stemming is a common technique in NLP, which suggests the involvement of computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.NE.
